               <msContents>
                  <summary>An isolated second volume of the <title>Ḥabīb al-Siyar</title> (Beloved
                     of Biographies), originally completed in <date calendar="Hijri-qamari"
                        from="1530" to="1540">937 AH (1530–1531 CE)</date> by <persName
                        key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/"
                        xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ibn Humām al-Dīn (ca.
                        1475–1535)</persName> known as <addName key="person_45109504"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/">Khvāndamīr (1487–1524 CE)</addName>,
                     a maternal grandson of Timurid-era historian <persName role="asn"
                        key="person_175393012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/175393012">Mīrkhvānd
                        (1433–1498)</persName>. It presents a popular general history covering the
                     pre-Islamic period up to the reign of Shāh Ismāʿīl I. The entire work consists
                     of a preface, an introduction, followed by three volumes, containing four
                     sections each appended with lists of names of prominent figures associated with
                     specific periods, followed by an epilogue. This volume covers the early Islamic
                     period up until the reign of the last Khwarazmshāh <persName role="subject"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9442701">Jalāl al-Dīn Mingburnu (r.
                        1220–1231)</persName>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_971-item1">
                     <author key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Khvānd Mīr, Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn
                           ibn Humām al-Dīn, ca. 1475-1535?</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">خواند مير، غياث الدين بن همام الدين</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Khvāndamīr</persName><lb/>
                        <persName type="alt" xml:lang="fa">خواندمير</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_645">Ḥabīb al-Siyar</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_645">حبيب السير</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> الحمد الله الذی جعل للنبین لسانا علیه و بعث فی...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="450a" to="450a"> برگ ۴۵۰ر (folio 450a):</locus> ...مشرف باد
                        عنوان رسایل. </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon</colophon>
                     <note>For other copies of this work held in the Rylands see, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6647"><idno>Persian
                              MS 165</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6894">398</ref> and
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6895"
                           >399</ref> (3 volumes bound in two), <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7315">809</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7317"
                           >810</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7318">811</ref> (3
                        vols), <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7322"
                           >815</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7323">816</ref>, (3
                        vols. bound in 2), and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26572">972</ref>,
                        as well as <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26573"
                           >973</ref>, and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26573">974</ref> (2
                        vols). For a full analysis, see Bockholt. For English translations of select
                        extracts by <persName role="trl" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/29350435"
                           key="person_29350435">Henry Lushington</persName>, see Elliot and
                        Dowson.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
