               <history>
                  <origin>Probably completed in the <origPlace cert="high"
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208">Indian
                        subcontinent</origPlace>; undated, but possibly <origDate cert="medium"
                        calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1650" notAfter="1768">mid 16th to mid 17th
                        century</origDate>. </origin>
                  <provenance><p>Previously owned by <persName role="fmo seal"
                           key="person_122375965" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/122375965/"
                           >Jean-Baptiste Gentil (1726–1799 CE)</persName> as per his seal
                        impressions on folios <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> and <locus
                           from="3a" to="3a">3a</locus>. Presumably sold by Gentil before his death
                        or by his family thereafter; however the circumstances of the volume's
                        arrival in Britain remain unclear. Note that although <persName
                           key="person_f7838" role="cataloguer">Siavash Rafiee-Rad</persName>
                        implies that Samuel Robinson of Wilmslow formerly owned this manuscript, we
                        find no external nor internal evidence to suggest this.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Unknown. Probably transferred from the University of Manchester Library to
                        the <orgName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/#John_Rylands_Library">John
                           Rylands Library</orgName> after the institutions merged in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1972">1972</date>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
